snippet.textDisplay: This reminds me of a quick-ish story: my father served in the Vietnam war and spent most of it on an aircraft carrier around the African coast. Local villagers would paddle out in their canoes to barter with the servicemen and women. My dad saw one of them with this really cool machete. They agreed to barter it for only a few apples. Yes, apples. He was so excited when he got it, being a rare and possibly collectible piece. Well, when he got it, he saw a stamped imprint on the blade saying, "Made in Hartford, Conn." OUR HOMESTATE. Even the sheath was cheap plastic! It cost him 5 whole apples so whatever. Haha
